    43→// The CUDAHooksInterface is an omnibus interface for any CUDA functionality
    44→// which we may want to call into from CPU code (and thus must be dynamically
    45→// dispatched, to allow for separate compilation of CUDA code).  How do I
    46→// decide if a function should live in this class?  There are two tests:
    47→//
    48→//  1. Does the *implementation* of this function require linking against
    49→//     CUDA libraries?
    50→//
    51→//  2. Is this function *called* from non-CUDA ATen code?
    52→//
    53→// (2) should filter out many ostensible use-cases, since many times a CUDA
    54→// function provided by ATen is only really ever used by actual CUDA code.
    55→//
